    "body": "Currently, the spill framework will copy buffers from host or disk to GPU memory when requested via `getColumnarBatch` or `getDeviceMemoryBuffer`.\r\n\r\nThis can be counterproductive, especially if the object on the GPU is actually pretty fast to compute. So the proposal here is to learn what kinds of buffers fit the criteria of \"cheaper to re-create than deal with all the spilling unspilling\", and implement a change to the framework and an API to leverage it.",
